{
  "texts": [
    "To identify the effects of the most important input features on the predictions of the random forest models, we calculated the partial dependence (Hastie et al., 2001) and plotted the individual conditional expectation (Goldstein et al., 2014) for the most accurate random forest model selected for each P form.",
    "To generate the final maps of the P forms, we grouped the maps predicted by the selected models for each P form via the mean and calculate the standard error (both in mg kg -1).",
    "We used the topsoil bulk density from SoilGrids 2.0 (Poggio et al., 2021) to calculate the stocks of each P form in the topsoil (in Pg -petagrams).",
    "The steps involved in model training, testing, and selection and the selected models used for the prediction of P forms are summarized in Fig.",
    "We compared our final map of total P concentration with the map of He et al. (2021)."
  ]
}